# Pixie Girl Hub — Public Sales Landing app

# Backend Hub API base. In production the sales.* subdomain proxies /api/*
# to the Hub via the edge load balancer; this var is the upstream target
# for the Next.js rewrite in dev (and the server-side fetch in fetchCampaign).
HUB_API_URL=http://localhost:0000

# Optional: pin the brand for local development when no host resolver is
# running. Otherwise the Host header drives the brand resolver upstream.
# DEFAULT_BRAND=pixiegirl

# Optional dev-only fallback for the Meta (Facebook) Pixel id. In production the
# pixel id is resolved PER BRAND from the published landing config (Landing
# Studio → seo.metaPixelId), so this is only a convenience for local testing
# when the Hub API isn't seeded. Bare numeric id only — not the <script> block.
# Build-time + single value, so it cannot differ per brand: never the prod
# source of truth for the two-brand deployment.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FB_PIXEL_ID=
